RIFT VALLEY FEVER, ANIMAL - SOUTH AFRICA (02): CAMELIDAE
********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Mon, 31 Jan 2011
From: Sophette Gers <sophetteg@elsenburg.com>

Rift Valley fever in alpacas in South Africa
--------------------------------------------
Regarding your RFI in ProMED Digest V2011 #47 "Rift Valley fever in
South Africa" [archive no. 20110129.0350]:

I am a diagnostic veterinary pathologist and was involved in the
diagnosis of the initial RVF outbreak in Alpacas in the Western Cape
last year and on a different property this year.

None of the affected alpaca herds had been vaccinated against RVF.

In the 2010 outbreak, it was mostly yearling animals that were
affected(I have presented the macroscopic and histopathology findings
at the American College of Veterinary Pathologists' - ACVP meeting in
Baltimore, in October/November 2010). [See abstract below].

Preliminary investigations of the most recent outbreak (2011) seem to
be affecting more mature male animals. To my knowledge, RVF has not
been reported in alpacas before and there is also no registered
vaccine for use in camelids.

--
communicated by:
Dr Sophette Gers
State Veterinarian
Provincial Veterinary Laboratory
Department of Agriculture: Western Cape
Private Bag X5020, Stellenbosch, 7599, South Africa
email: <sophetteg@elsenburg.com>
